<P>
 Jesus of Montreal (Bravo Monday at 9:30 a.m.) unfolds as an intense young 
actor (Lothaire Bluteau) becomes caught up in his role as Jesus. The fun of 
Denys Arcand's lethal satire of contemporary popular culture doesn't disturb 
this 1989 French-Canadian film's essential core of spiritual reflection. 
</P>
<P>
 La Strada (Bravo Thursday at 6 p.m., Friday at midnight), the 1954 Fellini 
classic, teams Anthony Quinn as a brutal strongman who tours Italy as a wistful 
Giulietta Masina tags along. 
</P>
