HANDGUN HUMOR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 In publishing a cartoon depicting two young boys having lunch at an elementary 
school where one finds a .357 Magnum handgun packed in his lunch box, you have 
glorified a hideous nightmare that scares children and adults alike (Callahan, 
Feb. 6). Why poke fun at a parent's worst fear -- that of losing a child to 
violence? 
</P>
<P>
 SUZETTE KOESTER 
