<P>
 COLORADO DESERT WILDFLOWERS by Jon Mark Stewart (Jon Mark Stewart Photography, 
73-430 Indian Creek Way, Palm Desert, Calif. 92260: $12.95, plus $4 tax and 
shipping; illustrated, paperback original). The Colorado Desert encompasses 
much of southeastern California, parts of Arizona, the Baja peninsula and 
sections of northern Mexico. Its ordinarily bleak landscape produces a lovely 
array of wildflowers, most of which appear after the annual rainy season. The 
striking photographs in this handsome guide are arranged by the color of the 
flowers, rather than their botanical classifications, a sensible arrangement 
that makes it easy for hikers and amateur scientists to use. 
