<P>
 VIVE LES AMATEURS DU PIANO. Theo Lieven and Hannes Keller, piano, Jana Werner, 
soprano, Gunter Thomasberger and Attila Szekely, cello, Eric Kushner, horn.Vive 
les amateurs records 1. This recording is of interest mainly for the 
extramusical accomplishments of the German-born pianists, who have found fame 
and fortune through their mathematical and entrepreneurial talents. 
Nevertheless, despite the flawed and often lackluster performances here -- that 
even the collaboration of three members of the Vienna Symphony, for Schumann's 
Andante and Variations cannot salvage -- there is an apparent joy in the 
process with which many amateurs may identify. Heller does offer a slightly 
unsteady but delicate and reasonably convincing Scarlatti sonata. "Es ist so 
leicht," from the musical "Nostalgie," by Alexis Weissenberg, who encouraged 
the making of this recording, stands out for its simplicity, conveyed by 
Werner's clear, reedy and innocent-sounding soprano. SUSAN BLISS 
