CRITICS' PICKS: 'AN ANGEL AT MY TABLE' 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Kevin Thomas 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Made by "Sweetie" and "The Piano's" iconoclastic Jane Campion, this remarkable 
1990 release is an amazing biography of Janet Frame, New Zealand's most 
celebrated novelist and poet whose struggles as an artist are intensified by 
her long ordeal as an incorrectly diagnosed schizophrenic. It stars Kerry Fox 
in a portrayal that is both heroic and profoundly illuminating. Karen Fergusson 
(center) plays Frame as a child (Bravo Friday at 6 p.m.). Kevin Thomas 
