<HEADLINE>
<P>
FROM THE HOME OFFICE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 I would like to thank Rick Du Brow for his fair and unbiased cover story on 
David Letterman ("Dave's Six-Month Checkup," Feb. 20). I get so tired of 
reading all of the rags' gossip about the late-night competition, and this was 
a very informative article. 
</P>
<P>
 I would also like to thank Howard Rosenberg for his commentary on what makes 
Dave watchable. I am a great fan of Letterman, and 99% of my friends think I'm 
nuts. But Rosenberg put it perfectly -- Dave's absurd and knows how to make 
absurdity an art form. 
</P>
<P>
 DONNA ANDERSON 
</P>
<P>
 Westchester 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Letterman is funny, witty and thoroughly entertaining. He is superb! The only 
reason I don't watch him -- Jay Leno is better. 
</P>
<P>
 ARTHUR LACHER 
</P>
<P>
 North Hollywood 
