<HEADLINE>
<P>
OLYMPIC AUDITORIUM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * As a former spectator of events at the Olympic Auditorium, I was happy to 
read Tim Kawakami's article about current efforts to revive and reopen that 
arena. However, your history summary states: "1945: The Olympic Auditorium 
begins wrestling shows, promoted by Eaton. . . ." This gives the impression 
that there was no wrestling at the Olympic prior to 1945.I saw wrestling 
matches there from the '30s up to World War II, promoted by Jack Daro. Among 
the wrestling notables I saw in the Olympic ring during this period were Jimmy 
Londos and Sandor Szabo, as well as former football star Bronco Nagurski and 
former heavyweight boxing title contender, George Godfrey. These old-timers, 
and many more, from the Olympic's pre-baby-boomer past may be unknown to 
younger generations, but they were there! 
</P>
<P>
 MARCUS A. KELLMAN 
</P>
<P>
 Torrance 
</P>
