<HEADLINE>
<P>
ENVIRONMENT: NOTES ABOUT YOUR SURROUNDINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Bay Tours -- A guided tour of the Upper Newport Bay Ecological Reserve will be 
offered Saturday, beginning at 9 a.m. 
</P>
<P>
 The tour is free and lasts about 2 1/2 hours. 
</P>
<P>
 Those who would like to participate are asked to meet at Shellmaker Island off 
Backbay Drive in Newport Beach.For more information, call (714) 640-6746. 
Caspers Field Trip -- South Coast Audubon, a chapter of the National Audubon 
Society, will hold a field trip Saturday to Ronald W. Caspers Regional Park. 
</P>
<P>
 The trip will begin at 8 a.m. 
</P>
<P>
 A lot of rain has produced an abundance of vegetation at the park, chapter 
officials said, creating favorable conditions for a variety of wildlife. Some 
unexpected bird species were recently spotted wintering in the park, and 
leaders hope for that to be true also during Saturday's trip. 
</P>
<P>
 Park entrance is limited to those 18 and over. There's a $2 entrance fee. 
</P>
<P>
 The park is at 33401 Ortega Highway, about 7 1/2 miles east of Interstate 5. 
Participants are asked to meet in the parking area left of the park's gate. 
</P>
