<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: FILLMORE; DISTRICT ANNOUNCES STAFF RESTRUCTURING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CONSTANCE SOMMER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Fillmore school officials announced a major administrative restructuring last 
week, shortly after the state released the results of a new test that ranked 
the district's students among the lowest in Ventura County. 
</P>
<P>
 "Essentially, we are calling ourselves to action," Assistant Supt.Mario 
Contini said. Contini will take over as the district's top administrator this 
summer. 
</P>
<P>
 The shuffle, effective July 1, will elevate Piru Elementary School Principal 
Jane Kampbell to assistant superintendent. Marsha Porter, principal at Sespe 
Elementary School, will take over Kampbell's job. Susan Dollar, now a teacher 
at Sespe, will become the Sespe principal. 
</P>
<P>
 Contini said he chose Kampbell as his second-in-command, rather than an 
outsider, because of the excellent job she had done at Piru. In last spring's 
statewide exams, Piru fourth-graders achieved some of the highest scores in the 
district on the reading test and even surpassed statewide averages. 
</P>
<P>
 Porter will move to Piru, he said, to provide continuity and allow the school 
to continue its improvements. CONSTANCE SOMMER 
</P>
</TEXT>
