<TEXT>
<P>
 Ventura police are looking for a teen-ager who stabbed an 18-year-old Domino's 
Pizza employee at the restaurant on East Thompson Boulevard, officers said. 
</P>
<P>
 Jeffrey Savaglio was working at Domino's Friday night when a youth, described 
as a 15- to 17-year-old white male with brown hair, and several of his friends 
entered the restaurant and confronted Savaglio about a recent arrest of one of 
their friends, Officer Kelly Dean said. 
</P>
<P>
 A fight broke out, and Savaglio was stabbed in the abdomen, Dean said. The 
assailants fled before officers arrived.  
</P>
<P>
 Savaglio was taken to Community Memorial Hospital, where he was treated and 
released Friday night, a hospital spokeswoman said. 
</P>
<P>
 Savaglio told Ventura police officers that he did not know the youth who 
attacked him, but could identify him. He told officers the teen-ager drove away 
in a late-model white car. TRACY WILSON 
