<P>
WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: OJAI; SUSPECTED ARSON FIRE DESTROYS 3-STORY BARN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SCOTT HADLY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Ventura County Fire Department is investigating a suspected arson fire 
that burned down a large wooden barn alongside the Ventura River near Ojai on 
Saturday, a department spokeswoman said. 
</P>
<P>
 The fire that ignited about 2:30 p.m. destroyed the three-story structure at 2 
Puesta Del Sol, causing $75,000 in damage, the spokeswoman said. 
</P>
<P>
 Neighbors reported seeing smoke and then large flames whipped by the strong 
afternoon winds. As ash from the fire dropped from the sky, a few of those 
living in the area took the precaution of watering down areas around their 
homes, according to the fire official. 
</P>
<P>
 Three engines responded to the blaze, but firefighters were unable to save the 
building, the spokeswoman said. The damage estimate includes $25,000 in farm 
equipment. No one was injured in the fire. SCOTT HADLY 
