<P>
TUSTIN SWIM TEAM WINS CHAMPIONSHIP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BERT ELJERA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A local team won the championship in an age-group swimming meet last month in 
Arizona, where 25 teams from Arizona, California and Nevada competed. 
</P>
<P>
 Six swimmers from the Southern California Aquatics Assn. of Tustin won medals 
in the Lost Dutchman invitational swimming championship held at Arizona State 
University's swim stadium Feb. 18 to 21. 
</P>
<P>
 Ryan Utsumi captured the gold in the boys 13- to 14-year-old bracket to lead 
the Tustin team to the overall championship. 
</P>
<P>
 Four of Utsumi's teammates won a silver, and one received a bronze. Fifty-five 
swimmers represented the team, which is also the Orange County champion. The 
silver medalists were Cory Tague, Robert Arroyo, Maikhanh Nguyen and Jarrod 
Cruzat. Chris Meyer won a bronze. 
</P>
<P>
 "It was a great team effort," said Everett Uchiyama, the team's head coach. 
</P>
<P>
 The team, which has 150 members, works out at the Foothill and Tustin high 
school pools. There are 115 members from Tustin and Santa Ana. The rest are 
from around the county, Uchiyama said. BERT ELJERA 
</P>
