<P>
BOYS' BASKETBALL / SOUTHERN REGIONAL ROUNDUP; LATE RALLY BY VERBUM DEI FALLS 
SHORT BY ONE POINT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By WENDY WITHERSPOON and MICHAEL ITAGAKI 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 San Diego Lincoln Prep led for most of the game and withstood a late rally to 
defeat Verbum Dei, 94-93, and win the Southern Regional Division IV boys' 
basketball championship Saturday night at Cal State Dominguez Hills. 
</P>
<P>
 Louis Johnson made the second of two free throws with 15 seconds to play, 
breaking a 93-93 tie. 
</P>
<P>
 Verbum Dei opted not to use its one remaining timeout and tried to run a fast 
break, but Andre Larry's shot was blocked by Mark Sanford. 
</P>
<P>
 Lincoln Prep's Deshawn Degrate grabbed the ball and threw it to the other end 
of the court as time expired. 
</P>
<P>
 Sanford had a game-high 32 points and 19 rebounds for Lincoln Prep (24-7). 
</P>
<P>
 Andre Miller led Verbum Dei (26-3) with 29 points and 11 rebounds. Teammate 
Jamal Cobbs scored 24 points. DIVISION III 
</P>
<P>
 Garden Grove Pacifica 60, University of San Diego High 55 -- Pacifica (30-1) 
rallied from an 11-point halftime deficit and Chris Vlasic made both ends of 
four consecutive one-and-ones in the final 1:08 at the Anaheim Arena. 
</P>
<P>
 Vlasic, Jon Surface, and Erik Maurer each scored 15 points for Pacifica, which 
forced nine turnovers in the third quarter and took a 44-42 lead into the 
fourth. 
</P>
<P>
 Pacifica made only one shot in the fourth quarter, but made all 14 of its free 
throws. 
</P>
<P>
 After Clint Cummings, who scored 16 points for USDHS, made one of two free 
throws to tie the score at 52-52 with 2:05 to play, the Dons (28-4) missed 
their next three shots and didn't score again until Josh Merrill made a 30-foot 
shot at the buzzer. 
</P>
<P>
 Merrill, a 6-foot-9 forward who has signed with Pepperdine, scored 10 of his 
17 points in the first quarter as the Dons took a 14-6 lead. 
</P>
<P>
 Mauricio Perez made a 25-foot shot at the halftime buzzer to give USDHS a 
35-24 lead, but Pacifica's defense clamped down after that. DIVISION V 
</P>
<P>
 Pacific Hills 74, Reedley Immanuel 51 -- Danny Brummel, a 6-4 senior forward, 
scored 27 points to lead Pacific Hills (24-8) at Cal State Dominguez Hills. 
</P>
<P>
 Westley Allen scored 21 points and Bryan Sterling 20 for the Bruins, who made 
33 of 43 shots. 
</P>
<P>
 Brummel made 12 of 14 shots. 
</P>
<P>
 Brad Robb, Jeff Holman and Todd Croissant each scored 10 points for Reedley 
Immanuel (27-5). WENDY WITHERSPOON and MICHAEL ITAGAKI 
</P>
