<HEADLINE>
<P>
GIRLS' BASKETBALL / SOUTHERN REGIONAL ROUNDUP; WOODBRIDGE CHARGES IN BATTLE OF 
UNBEATENS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By KENNEDY COSGROVE and MARTIN HENDERSON and WENDY WITHERSPOON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Irvine Woodbridge High took a giant step toward a Division II State 
championship by defeating previously unbeaten Mission Hills Alemany, 46-41, at 
Anaheim Arena on Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
 The Warriors (32-0) scored the last seven points of the State Southern 
Regional final, holding the Indians (30-1) scoreless over the final 2 minutes 
40 seconds. 
</P>
<P>
 Woodbridge will face Sacramento El Camino in the State championship game next 
Friday in Oakland. 
</P>
<P>
 Jamie Oenning made a jump shot with 1:25 remaining to give Woodbridge a 44-41 
lead. 
</P>
<P>
 "You go to your best shooter down the stretch," Coach Eric Bangs said. "That 
was the clutch shot. That was big." 
</P>
<P>
 Woodbridge center Angela Burgess scored a game-high 12 points and had seven 
offensive rebounds. 
</P>
<P>
 Alemany was led by center Carly Funicello's 12 points and eight rebounds. 
DIVISION III 
</P>
<P>
 Brea-Olinda 67, Newport Harbor 39 -- The nation's second-ranked team had no 
problem advancing to the State Division III championship. 
</P>
<P>
 The 28-point margin was the closest game the Ladycats had in seven playoff 
victories. They have won 53 games in a row. 
</P>
<P>
 Brea (32-0) won the Southern Section III-AA title a week earlier with a 70-40 
victory over Newport Harbor (24-8) and did nothing different this time. 
</P>
<P>
 Nicole Erickson scored 14 points and had 14 assists for the Ladycats. 
</P>
<P>
 Sarah Beckley had a game-high 17 points and 10 rebounds, and Colleen Hudson 
had 16 points. DIVISION IV 
</P>
<P>
 St. Bernard 54, Santa Ynez 41 -- Olympia Scott scored a game-high 25 points 
and also grabbed 12 rebounds to lead St. Bernard to its second consecutive 
Division IV Southern Regional victory before 1,347 at Cal State Dominguez 
Hills. 
</P>
<P>
 St. Bernard got in early foul trouble and Santa Ynez (26-6) took a 21-18 
halftime lead, sparked by 10 points by Sherry Bjorklund. 
</P>
<P>
 But Scott scored 14 points in the third quarter, when St. Bernard (27-4) 
outscored Santa Ynez, 20-14, to take a 38-35 lead. 
</P>
<P>
 Marte Alexander scored the first seven points of the fourth quarter to open up 
a 10-point lead for St. Bernard. DIVISION V 
</P>
<P>
 El Cajon Christian 53, La Jolla The Bishop's 48 -- Alisha Nater, a 6-foot-2 
junior forward, scored 17 points and grabbed 11 rebounds and Theresa Kain added 
16 points to lead Christian (28-4) to its second consecutive Southern Regional 
title. 
</P>
<P>
 Richelle Perkins scored 18 points for The Bishop's (27-4). KENNEDY COSGROVE 
and MARTIN HENDERSON and WENDY WITHERSPOON 
</P>
</TEXT>
