<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP BASKETBALL REGIONAL CHAMPIONSHIPS; BRUIN-TO-BE HENDERSON LEADS EAST 
BAKERSFIELD PAST INGLEWOOD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BARRY BAUM 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The defense changed. The momentum changed. The lead changed. 
</P>
<P>
 But the one constant was J.R. Henderson, who led East Bakersfield to its first 
Southern California Regional Division II championship with an 80-65 victory 
over top-seeded Inglewood Saturday at Anaheim Arena. 
</P>
<P>
 The second-seeded Blades (28-4) advance to play Roseville Oakmont (31-3) in 
the State Division II final Friday night at the Oakland Coliseum Arena.  
</P>
<P>
 Henderson, a 6-foot-9 senior who has signed with UCLA, scored a game-high 32 
points on 11-of-18 shooting and also had 13 rebounds and four blocked shots. 
His quickness and strength inside were too much for Inglewood, which double- 
and triple-teamed him. 
</P>
<P>
 "We tried to push him out," said Inglewood Coach Patrick Roy. 
</P>
<P>
 But even outside, Henderson frustrated the Sentinels by making two of three 
three-point shots. He also made all eight of his free throws, including six in 
the final two minutes. 
</P>
<P>
 The Blades' defense managed to slow Inglewood junior Paul Pierce, who scored 
only five of his 21 points in the last 11 minutes. 
</P>
<P>
 In the Division I girls' game: 
</P>
<P>
 Lynwood 62, Fresno Clovis West 51 -- Timicha Kirby scored 17 of her game-high 
29 points in the second half as the second-ranked Knights (32-1) earned the 
right to defend their Division I state championship against Atherton Sacred 
Heart. 
</P>
<P>
 In the Division IV boys' games: 
</P>
<P>
 San Diego Lincoln Prep 94, Verbum Dei 93 -- Lincoln Prep led for most of the 
game and withstood a late rally at Cal State Dominguez Hills. 
</P>
<P>
 In the Division IV girls' games: 
</P>
<P>
 St. Bernard 54, Santa Ynez 41 -- Olympia Scott scored a game-high 25 points 
and also grabbed 12 rebounds to lead St. Bernard (27-4) to its second 
consecutive Division IV title, at Cal State Dominguez Hills. 
</P>
<P>
 In the Division V boys' games: 
</P>
<P>
 Pacific Hills 74, Reedley Immanuel 51 -- Danny Brummel, a 6-4 senior forward, 
scored 27 points to lead Pacific Hills (24-8) at Cal State Dominguez Hills. 
</P>
<P>
 In the Division V girls' games: 
</P>
<P>
 El Cajon Christian 53, La Jolla The Bishop's 48 -- Alisha Nater, a 6-foot-2 
junior forward, scored 17 points and grabbed 11 rebounds to lead Christian 
(28-4) to its second consecutive regional title. BARRY BAUM 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Game Story 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA031394-0263 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 022431 </DOCID>
<SOURCE>
<P>
 Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</SOURCE>
<DATE>
<P>
March 13, 1994, Sunday, Orange County Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
