<HEADLINE>
<P>
KURTELA WINS TWO SPRINTS AT TITAN MEET 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 UC Irvine's Pam Kurtela won the women's 200 and 400 meters Saturday in the 
Titan Invitational track and field meet at Cal State Fullerton. 
</P>
<P>
 Kurtela's time of 24.72 seconds led an Irvine sweep in the 200; she was 
followed by Andrea Dean (25.24) and Jamie Karrer (25.62).Kurtela ran the 400 in 
57.45. 
</P>
<P>
 Athletes from Taft Community College dominated the men's sprints, winning the 
100, 200, 400 and 800 and both relays. Taft's Steven King easily won the 100 by 
two-tenths of a second in 10.47. 
</P>
<P>
 Luketz Swartbooi of Reebok posted another of the day's top men's times, 
winning the 5,000 in 13:46.91. 
</P>
<P>
 Rob Chronister, competing unattached, won the men's discus (165 feet 10 1/2 
inches) and shotput (59-0). 
</P>
</TEXT>
