<HEADLINE>
<P>
VARGAS, WHITAKER BOX TO U.S. AMATEUR TITLES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Two area boxers won title bouts in the U.S. Amateur Boxing championships 
Saturday in Colorado Springs. 
</P>
<P>
 Fernando Vargas of Oxnard won the 132-pound title by outpointing Terrence 
Cauthen of Philadelphia, 34-14. 
</P>
<P>
 Lance Whitaker of Northridge was the winner in the over 201-pound division by 
outpointing Robert Geer of San Jose, 20-15. 
</P>
<P>
 Vargas, 16, making his first appearance at the championships, was the youngest 
fighter in the final round. "To win an open tournament in your first try, I 
feel so great," said Vargas, who backed up Cauthen with rights to the head and 
knocked him down in the second round. "I could have stayed in the juniors, but 
I wanted to be with the big boys so I can try to get to the 1996 Olympics." 
</P>
</TEXT>
