four RBIs to lead St. Genevieve. TRACK & FIELD 
</P>
<P>
 Northridge-Alemany Relays -- Hurdlers Danny Haag of Granada Hills and Cathy 
Prater of Agoura turned in the top marks by local athletes in the meet at CSUN. 
</P>
<P>
 Haag was victorious in the 110-meter highs and the 300 intermediates, running 
a wind-aided 14.88 seconds in the former and a personal best of 39.13 in the 
latter. 
</P>
<P>
 Prater ran 44.6 to finish second in the 300 low hurdles and timed a wind-aided 
15.40 to place third in the 100 highs. SOFTBALL 
</P>
<P>
