<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP BASEBALL ROUNDUP; SPRAIN'S TWO-HITTER, ZAMORA'S HOMER WIN FOR CAPISTRANO 
VALLEY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By FORREST LEE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Bobby Sprain threw a two-hitter, and Pete Zamora homered for the third 
consecutive game as Capistrano Valley shut out Mater Dei, 2-0, for the 
championship of the Newport Elks baseball tournament Saturday at Tustin High. 
</P>
<P>
 Sprain (1-0) pitched out of a bases-loaded jam in the first inning and 
dominated the rest of the way in a matchup of two clubs expected to contend for 
the South Coast League title. 
</P>
<P>
 He limited the Monarchs (2-1-1) to one hit during the final six innings and 
retired 10 of the last 11 batters as Capistrano Valley (4-0), ranked fifth in 
Southern Section Division I, prevented Mater Dei from repeating as tournament 
champion. 
</P>
<P>
 "You can't win many ballgames if you just get two hits," Mater Dei Coach Bob 
Ickes said. "We just didn't swing the bats. We made 11 outs on popups." 
</P>
<P>
 Mater Dei starter Matt Treanor (0-1) was effective early before giving up the 
game-winning homer to Zamora in the third. With two outs, after Treanor hit 
Gabe Payne with a pitch, Zamora hit a fastball out over the right-field fence. 
</P>
<P>
 Sprain kept the Cougars in command from there. After a walk, a single and a 
hit batter in the first, Sprain allowed two baserunners in the final five 
innings, giving up a single in the fourth and a walk in the fifth. He struck 
out three and walked three. 
</P>
<P>
 In the third-place game: 
</P>
<P>
 Esperanza 5, Tustin 4 -- Greg Smith drove in the winning run for Esperanza 
(3-1) in the bottom of the seventh with two outs to capture third place. Smith 
was two for three with two runs batted in. Jason Webb went three for four, with 
two RBIs. 
</P>
<P>
 In the consolation championship game: 
</P>
<P>
 Corona del Mar 6, Trabuco Hills 1 -- Kevin Stuart threw a four-hitter with six 
strikeouts and Jim Huston had three RBIs for Corona del Mar (4-2). 
</P>
<P>
 In first round of the Redlands Calvary Chapel tournament: 
</P>
<P>
 Redlands Calvary Chapel 4, Liberty Christian 3 -- Greg Rule struck out 10 and 
walked one for Liberty Christian (2-2), which loaded the bases in the top of 
the seventh but was unable to score. 
</P>
<P>
 In the third-place game of the Duarte tournament: 
</P>
<P>
 Rancho Alamitos 6, Duarte 9 -- Jose Castro (1-0) struck out seven in five 
scoreless innings and Brett Osterode drove in four runs on two doubles for 
Rancho Alamitos (3-1). 
</P>
<P>
 In nonleague games: 
</P>
<P>
 La Habra 6-11, Valencia 1-9 -- Jeremy Payne picked up saves in both games and 
Ken Huff had five hits, including two doubles and five RBIs for La Habra (2-0). 
</P>
<P>
 Troy 10-2, Santa Margarita 3-1 -- Brad Downing had three hits, including a 
home run, and three RBIs in the first game and Rick Parmenter threw a 
one-hitter, striking out nine in the second for Troy. FORREST LEE 
</P>
