<HEADLINE>
<P>
2,700 HELD IN BOMBAY ON BOMBINGS ANNIVERSARY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Police have taken at least 2,700 people into custody as "a precautionary 
measure" on the anniversary of bombings that killed 257 people, police said 
Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
 On March 12, 1993, Bombay was rocked by 13 bomb explosions. Police blame the 
blasts on Muslim radicals taking revenge for the demolition of a mosque by 
Hindu zealots. 
</P>
<P>
 Most of those detained in the past 10 days are considered habitual offenders 
by police. They have not been formally charged but are being kept in police 
lockups. 
</P>
