<HEADLINE>
<P>
MYANMAR ASSAILS IDEA OF RADIO FREE ASIA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Myanmar's military government criticized a U.S. move to set up a radio service 
to promote democracy in Asia, state-run radio reported Friday. 
</P>
<P>
 The broadcast quoted an unnamed foreign ministry official as telling a U.S. 
diplomat that the Senate's Feb. 2 decision to set up Radio Free Asia was 
"unjustifiable" and would not be helpful for relations between the two 
countries. 
</P>
<P>
 The U.S. government-run station would be aimed at Myanmar, China, North Korea, 
Cambodia, Laos and Vietnam. 
</P>
