<HEADLINE>
<P>
SELLERS CAN GET HELP FROM PROS AT SATURDAY'S FAIR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Even though the housing market is warming up in many Southland communities, 
selling a home is still a tremendous challenge. But savvy advice can make it 
less of an ordeal. 
</P>
<P>
 At the fifth annual Times' Home Buyers and Sellers Fair, sellers will get tips 
from experts on how to best present their home in a sluggish real estate 
market. And they can learn what the pros think about how the Northridge 
earthquake will affect home sales and prices in the region. 
</P>
<P>
 The one-day consumer education event, the largest of its kind in the country, 
will be held from 9:30 a.m. to 5:30 p.m. Saturday at the Anaheim Convention 
Center. 
</P>
<P>
 Times' "Starting Out" columnist Dian Hymer, author of "Buying and Selling a 
Home in California," will conduct a special workshop for sellers on how to 
price their homes, prepare the home for sale and closing the deal. Joining her 
will be Dan Lieberman, co-author of "Getting the Most for Your Home in a Down 
Market."  
</P>
<P>
 For details, please see ad on K6-K7. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA031394-0311 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 022480 </DOCID>
<SOURCE>
<P>
 Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</SOURCE>
<DATE>
<P>
March 13, 1994, Sunday, Home Edition Correction Appended 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
Real Estate; Part K; Page 1; Column 2; Real Estate Desk 
