GARDENER'S CHECKLIST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 For dedicated gardeners, here are suggestions from the California Assn. of 
Nurserymen on what to do in the garden this week:  
</P>
<P>
 * If you started vegetable seeds already, be sure to thin them to prevent 
overcrowding or stunted plants.Do this when the plants are two to three inches 
high. 
</P>
<P>
 * Give your lawn a boost this spring by starting a regular feeding program 
now. 
</P>
<P>
 * Pinching annuals at planting time will give you a bigger and better bloom 
later. 
</P>
<P>
 * Let the kids in on the fun of a vegetable garden. Quick results are seen 
from planting radish seeds and this keeps their interest while the others grow. 
</P>
