<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORE ON THE WOLVES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 I have spent several summers in Alaska and I am concerned about the frequently 
suggested boycotting of Alaskan tourism (Letters, Feb. 28). There are many 
small businesses in Alaska that depend upon tourism and that have little 
control over state governmental decisions.A universal boycott is irresponsible 
and threatens to destroy businesses that should be supported as environmentally 
responsible, sensitive and constructive. Instead, write to the Alaska Division 
of Tourism and tell them that you are not going on that expensive luxury cruise 
to Alaska. Tell them -- and do it -- that you are instead going on an 
eco-sensitive wilderness tour to view wolves, whales, sea otters and bears, and 
that you will insist upon a pristine wilderness experience. 
</P>
<P>
 JAMES L. VERMILLION 
</P>
</TEXT>
