<P>
MAN'S DEATH IN JAIL WARD INVESTIGATED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ADRIAN MAHER, SPECIAL TO THE TIMES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Los Angeles County Sheriff's Department homicide detectives this week 
continued to investigate the death of a 41-year-old man in officers' custody at 
County-USC Medical Center. 
</P>
<P>
 John Bernard Wiley Jr. of Mar Vista died at 8:46 p.m. Friday after a struggle 
with officers in the hospital's jail ward, Deputy Gabe Ramirez said. 
</P>
<P>
 Deputies arrested Wiley at 4:38 p.m. Friday after responding to a report of a 
domestic dispute in the 12200 block of Pacific Avenue. 
</P>
<P>
 While Wiley was being restrained, a struggle ensued and a police officer was 
assaulted, Ramirez said. Wiley reportedly fell down a flight of stairs and 
received a cut on the back of his head. 
</P>
<P>
 He was arrested and transported to the County-USC jail ward for treatment and 
booking. 
</P>
<P>
 Wiley "became combative after his handcuffs were removed" at the hospital, 
Ramirez said. Several deputies and a Los Angeles Police Department officer were 
attempting to restrain him when he stopped breathing, Ramirez said. 
</P>
<P>
 Doctors could not revive Wiley, Ramirez said. 
</P>
<P>
 Scott Carrier, spokesman for the coroner's office, said an autopsy has been 
completed. The cause of death will be determined after toxicology results are 
received. 
