<DATE>
<P>
March 13, 1994, Sunday, Home Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
Part A; Page 1; Column 1; Metro Desk 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
2232 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLUMN ONE; A TRIBE'S BATTLE FOR ITS IDENTITY; OVER THE YEARS, THE JUANENO 
INDIANS WERE STRIPPED OF A LARGE PART OF SOUTHERN CALIFORNIA. THEY SEEK U.S. 
RECOGNITION TO VALIDATE THEIR PAST AND ENRICH THEIR FUTURE. 
</P>
