<HEADLINE>
<P>
READERS RECOMMEND 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 California -- Harriet Mills, Paso Robles: "Pelargonium Restaurant, 51 Hanford 
St., Sutter Creek 95685; (209) 267-5008.An exceptional restaurant. Cheese 
ravioli Alfredo melted in my mouth." Dinner prices range from $14-$19. 
</P>
<P>
 Canada -- Gerry and Herb Holley, Mercer Island, Wash.: "Mark Ranson, 1663 
Rockland Ave., No. 4, Victoria, B.C. V8S 1W6; (604) 592-0313. We chartered his 
48-foot sailboat to tour the Gulf Islands of British Columbia. He's a fabulous 
captain, chef and host." Rates: $2,100 for two couples for a week, inclusive. 
</P>
<P>
 Ireland -- Joan Belisle, Laguna Hills: "Castle Oaks Hotel, Castle Connell, 
County Limerick; tel. 011-353-61-377666, fax 011-353-61-377717. Converted 
Georgian mansion on Shannon River with health club, tennis, fishing, wonderful 
food." Summer rates: Doubles start at about $100 per night. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA031394-0402 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 022573 </DOCID>
<SOURCE>
<P>
 Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</SOURCE>
<DATE>
<P>
March 13, 1994, Sunday, Home Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
